  "text": "The LibreOffice Core document model architecture is built on these five key C++ classes:\n\n1. **SfxObjectShell** (include/sfx2/objsh.hxx, line 170): The base class for all document shells in LibreOffice. This is the fundamental class that all document types (Writer, Calc, Impress, Draw) inherit from. It provides the core document framework functionality including loading, saving, and managing document properties.\n\n2. **SwDoc** (sw/inc/doc.hxx, line 196): The Writer (word processor) document class. This represents a complete Writer document and contains the document content, formatting, styles, and all word processor-specific features.\n\n3. **ScDocument** (sc/inc/document.hxx, line 331): The Calc (spreadsheet) document class. This represents a complete Calc spreadsheet document with all sheets, cells, formulas, and calculation engine functionality.\n\n4. **SdDrawDocument** (sd/inc/drawdoc.hxx, line 338): The Impress/Draw document class. Inherits from FmFormModel and represents presentation or drawing documents with slides/pages, shapes, and drawing objects.\n\n5. **SfxApplication** (include/sfx2/app.hxx, line 103): The LibreOffice application framework entry point. This class inherits from SfxShell and manages the overall application lifecycle, including initialization, window management, and document creation.\n\nThe architecture follows a hierarchical design where SfxObjectShell serves as the base for all module-specific document classes, allowing LibreOffice to maintain a unified framework while supporting different document types with specialized features."
}

